 &quot;In an almost forgotten example of inter-American cooperation, representatives from Argentina, Brazil, and Chile (the A.B.C. powers) convened at Niagara Falls, Ontario, in 1914 to mediate the dispute arising from the Woodrow Wilson government's invasion of Veracruz during the Mexican Revolution. &quot; 
